description:
Victor Goines, clarinetist for the Jazz at Lincoln Center Orchestra, discusses New Orleans clarinet master Barney Bigard, and looks at his contributions to the ensembles of masters like Duke Ellington and Louis Armstrong!

Learn more at the Jazz Academy by visiting http://academy.jazz.org

Victor Goines - Clarinet
Eric Suquet - Director
Bill Thomas - Director of Photography
Rich Emery - Production Assistant
Seton Hawkins - Producer
